quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  5,83,"And when they hear what was sent down to the Messenger, you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>see their eyes overflowing with tears for what they recognize of the truth; they say, “Our Lord, we have attained faith, so write us down with those who bear witness."
  5,84,"And how should we not believe in Allah and what has come to us of the truth, andwe ardently hope that our Lord will enter us along with the righteous people<i class=""s"">(into Paradise) </i>?”"
  5,85,"So Allah rewarded them for what they said—Gardens beneath which rivers flow, abiding therein; and that is the repayment of those who excel in doing good."
  5,86,"But those who denied and disbelieved in Our signs—those are the fellows of purgatory."
  5,87,"O you who have attained faith, do not prohibit the good things Allah has made lawful for you, and do not transgress; indeed, Allah does not love the transgressors."
  5,88,"And eat of the lawful, good things Allah has provided for you, and be mindful of Allah in whom you are believers."
  5,89,"Allah does not hold you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>accountable for idle talk involving your oaths{1}, but He holds you accountable for your <span class=",footnotes:1:Unintended oaths.,footnotes:2:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Shu’ba, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…for your binding of oaths;” Ibn Zekwan read it as: “…for your sustained binding of oaths;”</span>,footnotes:3:Literally ‘a neck’.,footnotes:4:Literally ‘preserve'.
